<p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">The thread resisted, taut and unyielding, as if woven with iron. Pain, sharp and searing, shot through Elara's consciousness, mirroring the Cosmic Loom's violent rejection of her interference. It was like trying to untie a knot that had been tied by the universe itself. Her body trembled, sweat beaded on her brow, and a faint, shimmering crack appeared in her own silver-grey thread, a tiny fracture caused by the immense strain. But she persisted, fueled by Kael's imagined laughter, by the vibrant colors of his thread that refused to dim in her mind's eye. Slowly, agonizingly, inch by excruciating inch, the dark knot around Kael's thread began to loosen. The pattern of the market collapse, the specific angle of the falling beam, the moment of his demise – it began to blur, to shift, to rearrange. A tiny, almost imperceptible tremor ran through the entire Cosmic Tapestry.</p>
