<p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">She spent sleepless nights, the shimmering chaos of the Tapestry filling her mind. She tried to find a way to re-weave, to undo, but the threads seemed to mock her, becoming even more complex with each attempt. The weight of her responsibility became unbearable. She had wanted to save one life, and in doing so, had disrupted countless others. Her vision of destiny, once a clear map, had become a terrifying, uncontrollable storm of intersecting lines and unforeseen consequences. She longed for the serene detachment she had once possessed, but it was gone, irrevocably lost in the maelstrom of her own making.</p>

